Introduction
This project utilizes a simple linear regression model to predict salaries based on years of experience. It uses the Salary_Data.csv dataset containing two columns: "YearsExperience" and "Salary". The model is trained on this dataset and then used to predict salaries for new data points.

Installation
To use this project, follow these steps:

Clone the repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your_username/salary-prediction.git
Install the required dependencies:

Copy code
pip install numpy pandas matplotlib plotly scikit-learn
Usage
To run the model and predict salaries:

Ensure that the Salary_Data.csv file is in the same directory as the script.
Run the script:
Copy code
python predict_salary.py
Follow the on-screen instructions to input the years of experience for which you want to predict the salary.
Dependencies
Python 3.x
NumPy
Pandas
Matplotlib
Plotly
scikit-learn
